# Testing Rules

## Test Pyramid

| Layer | Annotation | What to test | Speed |
|-------|-----------|--------------|-------|
| Unit | `@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)` | Domain logic, application service | Fast |
| Slice | `@WebMvcTest`, `@DataJpaTest` | Controller, JPA queries | Medium |
| Integration | `@SpringBootTest` + Testcontainers | Full flow, DB, SQS | Slow |

## Naming Convention
```
MethodName_StateUnderTest_ExpectedBehavior
createOrder_withInvalidCustomerId_throwsDomainException
```

## Unit Test Pattern (Domain)
```java
class OrderTest {

    @Test
    void createOrder_withValidItems_setsStatusToPending() {
        // Given
        var items = List.of(new OrderItem(ProductId.of("P1"), 2, Money.of(50, "USD")));

        // When
        var order = Order.create(CustomerId.of("C1"), items);

        // Then
        assertThat(order.getStatus()).isEqualTo(OrderStatus.PENDING);
        assertThat(order.getTotalAmount()).isEqualTo(Money.of(100, "USD"));
    }

    @Test
    void createOrder_withEmptyItems_throwsDomainException() {
        assertThatThrownBy(() -> Order.create(CustomerId.of("C1"), List.of()))
            .isInstanceOf(DomainException.class)
            .hasMessage("Order must have at least one item");
    }
}
```

## Application Service Test Pattern
```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class OrderApplicationServiceTest {

    @Mock OrderRepository orderRepository;
    @Mock OrderEventPublisher eventPublisher;

    @InjectMocks OrderApplicationService service;

    @Test
    void createOrder_persistsAndPublishesEvent() {
        // Given
        var request = new CreateOrderRequest("customer-1", List.of(...));
        var savedOrder = Order.create(...);
        given(orderRepository.save(any())).willReturn(savedOrder);

        // When
        service.createOrder(request);

        // Then
        then(orderRepository).should().save(any(Order.class));
        then(eventPublisher).should().publishOrderCreated(savedOrder);
    }
}
```

## Controller Slice Test
```java
@WebMvcTest(OrderController.class)
class OrderControllerTest {

    @Autowired MockMvc mockMvc;
    @MockBean OrderApplicationService orderService;

    @Test
    void createOrder_withValidRequest_returns201() throws Exception {
        given(orderService.createOrder(any())).willReturn(new OrderResponse("order-1", ...));

        mockMvc.perform(post("/api/v1/orders")
                .contentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
                .content("""
                    {"customerId": "c1", "items": [{"productId": "p1", "quantity": 2}]}
                    """))
            .andExpect(status().isCreated())
            .andExpect(header().exists("Location"))
            .andExpect(jsonPath("$.orderId").value("order-1"));
    }
}
```

## Rules
- Domain layer: 100% unit test coverage (no mocking of domain)
- Application service: mock repositories and publishers
- Controller: `@WebMvcTest` only — no Spring context for unit tests
- Integration tests use Testcontainers (Postgres, LocalStack for SQS)
- Test data builders — no raw constructors in test setup

## Checklist before PR
- [ ] New domain logic has unit tests
- [ ] New endpoint has `@WebMvcTest` slice test
- [ ] Happy path + at least one failure path tested
- [ ] No `Thread.sleep()` in tests — use Awaitility for async
- [ ] Integration test added for cross-layer flows
